In a recent call with reporters, a senior administration official provided updates on the SolarWinds and Microsoft Exchange hacks. Regarding the SolarWinds incident, the official stated that the compromised agencies have completed an independent review to ensure the adversary has been eradicated. The government will be rolling out technology to address cybersecurity gaps and modernize federal defenses, starting with the nine compromised agencies. The official also mentioned plans to establish cybersecurity standards for software companies and create transparency in the market for cybersecurity. In terms of the Microsoft Exchange hack, the official highlighted the need to patch vulnerable servers promptly and work closely with Microsoft to secure federal systems. The government is also focused on enhancing public-private partnerships and improving information-sharing to address cybersecurity threats.